WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.260 --> 00:00:03.668
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: I thought before

00:00:03.668 --> 00:00:06.218
going into today's topic,
I will give you a five-minute

00:00:06.218 --> 00:00:08.060
summary of what happened last
time.

00:00:08.060 --> 00:00:11.223
So, you guys are saying,
"Look, it looks like you got

00:00:11.223 --> 00:00:15.028
carried away with this thing;
we just want to know what we

00:00:15.028 --> 00:00:18.250
need to become good doctors,
so just tell us."

00:00:18.250 --> 00:00:22.079
So, if you're a doctor or a
lawyer or -- I've had really

00:00:22.079 --> 00:00:26.256
strong students in my class who
had nothing to do with any of

00:00:26.256 --> 00:00:28.570
the sciences,
physics or chemistry,

00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:31.370
which of course is a great
pleasure for me to know.

00:00:31.370 --> 00:00:34.175
So, if you go forward into your
life's mission,

00:00:34.175 --> 00:00:36.920
what should you know from the
last lecture?

00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:41.462
Here's the main point.
The Law of Conservation of

00:00:41.462 --> 00:00:45.054
Energy is a powerful concept
that I told you,

00:00:45.054 --> 00:00:48.320
survives even the quantum
revolution.

00:00:48.320 --> 00:00:51.734
So, it looks like we may
ascribe to a system something

00:00:51.734 --> 00:00:55.181
called the total energy,
which is the kinetic energy,

00:00:55.181 --> 00:00:57.206
which is always Â½
mv^(2),

00:00:57.206 --> 00:01:00.750
and potential energy which
depends on the location of the

00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:03.166
object,
and it varies from problem to

00:01:03.166 --> 00:01:06.650
problem, depending on whether
they're connected to a spring or

00:01:06.650 --> 00:01:09.078
gravity and so on.
In one dimension,

00:01:09.078 --> 00:01:13.123
we could always get to the
potential energy for any force

00:01:13.123 --> 00:01:17.943
that depended only on location.
The trick was to go back to the

00:01:17.943 --> 00:01:21.526
Work Energy Theorem,
which just applies Newton's

00:01:21.526 --> 00:01:25.796
laws and says the change in
kinetic energy of the body is

00:01:25.796 --> 00:01:31.168
the work done by the body,
and that work we defined to be

00:01:31.168 --> 00:01:33.622
this;
then, the sum of all this,

00:01:33.622 --> 00:01:37.327
on the left-hand side,
would be the change in kinetic

00:01:37.327 --> 00:01:39.388
energy.
On the right-hand side,

00:01:39.388 --> 00:01:42.085
this would become an integral
of F, from

00:01:42.085 --> 00:01:44.900
x_1 to
x_2.

00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:48.070
And if F really is a
function of x and not of

00:01:48.070 --> 00:01:50.640
also velocity,
the laws of calculus tell you,

00:01:50.640 --> 00:01:53.240
you may write this integral as
the difference of two numbers.

00:01:56.379 --> 00:01:59.002
Then, you rearrange the
expression to get

00:01:59.002 --> 00:02:01.560
K_1 +
U_1;

00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:03.304
U_1 is
shorthand for U of

00:02:03.304 --> 00:02:05.673
x_1;
is K_2 +

00:02:05.673 --> 00:02:08.539
U_2.
And that means the energy

00:02:08.539 --> 00:02:11.615
E_1,
to begin with the energy at the

00:02:11.615 --> 00:02:14.299
end.
If there is a frictional force,

00:02:14.299 --> 00:02:18.107
then in this integral you break
it up into two parts:

00:02:18.107 --> 00:02:21.182
the part, say,
due to a spring and the part

00:02:21.182 --> 00:02:24.287
due to friction.
The part due to a spring will

00:02:24.287 --> 00:02:27.273
integrate to give you this.
Then, you'll still have the

00:02:27.273 --> 00:02:30.792
part due to friction left over.
In that case the result will

00:02:30.792 --> 00:02:34.590
look like (K_2 +
U_2) - (K_1

00:02:34.590 --> 00:02:37.334
+ U_1).
Instead of being zero,

00:02:37.334 --> 00:02:39.449
it will be the work done by
friction.

00:02:39.449 --> 00:02:43.283
We write it symbolically this
way but the frictional force is

00:02:43.283 --> 00:02:45.520
not a function of x
alone,

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:48.566
but if knew which path you're
taking and which way you're

00:02:48.566 --> 00:02:50.470
moving, you can do that
integral.

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:52.970
You want to do this in higher
dimensions.

00:02:52.970 --> 00:02:56.475
In higher dimensions,
what I found out was that if

00:02:56.475 --> 00:03:00.909
you wanted the change of kinetic
energy to be the work done,

00:03:00.909 --> 00:03:05.736
then what you had to do was to
write this expression,

00:03:05.736 --> 00:03:10.006
which was a shorthand for
F_x,

00:03:10.006 --> 00:03:15.103
dx + F_y dy.
So, you take a point and you go

00:03:15.103 --> 00:03:18.120
to a neighboring point,
that's the work done;

00:03:18.120 --> 00:03:20.958
and this work done was cooked
up so that it was a change in

00:03:20.958 --> 00:03:22.460
kinetic energy.
Then you say,

00:03:22.460 --> 00:03:25.349
okay, let me take a finite
path, starting with some point

00:03:25.349 --> 00:03:27.568
r_1 and going
to some point

00:03:27.568 --> 00:03:31.340
r_2.
Then, I add up all the changes.

00:03:31.340 --> 00:03:32.915
The left-hand side is
K_2 -

00:03:32.915 --> 00:03:34.894
K_1,
and the right-hand side is this

00:03:34.894 --> 00:03:35.420
integral.

00:03:39.610 --> 00:03:43.800
This is always true.
This will never be wrong.

00:03:43.800 --> 00:03:46.110
It's just a restatement of
Newton's law.

00:03:46.110 --> 00:03:50.432
The problem will be,
can we write this integral here

00:03:50.432 --> 00:03:54.440
as a difference of two numbers,
one depending on the starting

00:03:54.440 --> 00:03:56.320
point and one depending on the
ending point?

00:03:56.320 --> 00:04:00.590
Is this possible?
That's a question mark.

00:04:00.590 --> 00:04:02.255
If it's possible,
you are done,

00:04:02.255 --> 00:04:05.698
because you're back to writing
K_1 + U_1

00:04:05.698 --> 00:04:07.919
= K_2 +
U_2.

00:04:07.919 --> 00:04:11.348
But I tried to convince you
that it's not always going to

00:04:11.348 --> 00:04:13.746
happen.
So, let's understand why it's

00:04:13.746 --> 00:04:16.709
not always going to happen.
It is not enough in this

00:04:16.709 --> 00:04:18.919
integral to say,
start at r_1

00:04:18.919 --> 00:04:21.540
and go to r_2.
In fact, if I just said,

00:04:21.540 --> 00:04:23.679
find the integral of the work
done by the force between

00:04:23.679 --> 00:04:25.620
r_1 and
r_2,

00:04:25.620 --> 00:04:27.808
you will have to tell
me--you'll have to ask me

00:04:27.808 --> 00:04:29.790
something.
You agree?

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:33.208
What will you ask in addition,
besides just saying start at

00:04:33.208 --> 00:04:36.449
r_1 and end at
r_2?

00:04:36.449 --> 00:04:37.879
Student: What happens in
between.

00:04:37.879 --> 00:04:39.147
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: You will ask,

00:04:39.147 --> 00:04:41.239
"What path did you take?"
And unless you specify the path

00:04:41.239 --> 00:04:43.643
you cannot do the integral,
because you don't know what

00:04:43.643 --> 00:04:46.354
contour you want to draw.
Therefore, the answer in

00:04:46.354 --> 00:04:49.832
general depends on the path,
but this right-hand side does

00:04:49.832 --> 00:04:52.076
not.
So, if you pick the same two

00:04:52.076 --> 00:04:55.190
endpoints and you vary that path
into this one,

00:04:55.190 --> 00:04:57.459
the right-hand side doesn't
change, but it's not hard to

00:04:57.459 --> 00:04:59.440
imagine the left-hand side would
be different.

00:04:59.440 --> 00:05:02.230
Therefore, in general this will
not be true.

00:05:02.230 --> 00:05:04.986
So, even though there's a
relation between work done and

00:05:04.986 --> 00:05:08.589
increase in kinetic energy,
you will not get a law of

00:05:08.589 --> 00:05:12.459
conservation of energy,
unless this is true.

00:05:12.459 --> 00:05:15.328
Then I said,
there is still hope because we

00:05:15.328 --> 00:05:18.128
can, in fact,
manufacture forces for which

00:05:18.128 --> 00:05:20.784
this is true.
To manufacture the force,

00:05:20.784 --> 00:05:24.372
you pick any function U,
of x and y that

00:05:24.372 --> 00:05:27.185
you like,
then define a new force whose

00:05:27.185 --> 00:05:31.377
x component is minus the
derivative of U with

00:05:31.377 --> 00:05:34.662
respect to x,
and whose y component is

00:05:34.662 --> 00:05:37.331
the minus the derivative of
U with respect to

00:05:37.331 --> 00:05:39.495
y.
Then, you got to go back and

00:05:39.495 --> 00:05:42.839
look at your notes and see that
if you take F.dr now,

00:05:42.839 --> 00:05:45.543
you're just adding the change
in U, and when you go

00:05:45.543 --> 00:05:48.199
from start to finish the total
change will in fact be the

00:05:48.199 --> 00:05:50.221
change in U,
from start to finish,

00:05:50.221 --> 00:05:51.949
and won't depend on how you got
there.

00:05:51.949 --> 00:05:53.920
So basically,
what you're doing is,

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:57.457
in the xy plane you are
defining a function U of

00:05:57.457 --> 00:05:59.660
xy, which is like a
height.

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:03.143
You defined the force in a
clever way so that F.dr

00:06:03.143 --> 00:06:05.879
is the change in the height,
as you march.

00:06:05.879 --> 00:06:08.099
So, you can start at any point
on the mountain,

00:06:08.099 --> 00:06:10.029
go to any other point on the
mountain;

00:06:10.029 --> 00:06:12.885
if you're only keeping track of
the change in height you're

00:06:12.885 --> 00:06:15.839
going to get the same answer,
no matter how you got from here

00:06:15.839 --> 00:06:18.393
to there.
So, you start with a potential

00:06:18.393 --> 00:06:21.263
and work out a force,
and that force will then

00:06:21.263 --> 00:06:24.579
obviously give an answer that's
path independent,

00:06:24.579 --> 00:06:27.224
and the potential associated
with the force is the function

00:06:27.224 --> 00:06:28.693
you began with.
In other words,

00:06:28.693 --> 00:06:30.497
in this problem then,
K_1 +

00:06:30.497 --> 00:06:32.486
U_1 will be
K_2 +

00:06:32.486 --> 00:06:35.506
U_2,
where U is the same guy

00:06:35.506 --> 00:06:38.029
you began with.
So, you can get a law of

00:06:38.029 --> 00:06:40.310
conservation of energy in that
case.

00:06:40.310 --> 00:06:44.519
Then, I told you without proof
that this is the only way it can

00:06:44.519 --> 00:06:46.049
happen.
In other words,

00:06:46.049 --> 00:06:49.848
we all agree that if you got a
force from a potential by taking

00:06:49.848 --> 00:06:52.706
derivatives, it does the job.
But I'm saying,

00:06:52.706 --> 00:06:56.291
every force whose integral is
independent of path will always

00:06:56.291 --> 00:06:58.920
have as its ancestor a function
U,

00:06:58.920 --> 00:07:01.198
and the x component of
the force will be the x

00:07:01.198 --> 00:07:03.283
derivative of the function and
the y will be the

00:07:03.283 --> 00:07:05.352
y derivative.
That's not obvious,

00:07:05.352 --> 00:07:08.838
but in other words it's clear
it's sufficient but it's also

00:07:08.838 --> 00:07:11.665
necessary.
So, every conservative force is

00:07:11.665 --> 00:07:15.029
the derivative of some
potential, in this fashion.

00:07:15.029 --> 00:07:18.805
Finally, I said if someone
comes and gives you a force and

00:07:18.805 --> 00:07:21.189
says, "Is it conservative or
not?"

00:07:21.189 --> 00:07:24.389
either you can think in your
head and try to guess that

00:07:24.389 --> 00:07:27.174
function U,
of which this F is the

00:07:27.174 --> 00:07:29.813
derivative, in this fashion.
If you succeed,

00:07:29.813 --> 00:07:31.884
you know it's conservative;
if you fail,

00:07:31.884 --> 00:07:35.363
maybe it's not conservative or
maybe you are not clever enough

00:07:35.363 --> 00:07:38.600
in finding that function.
So, here is a recipe that works

00:07:38.600 --> 00:07:40.590
for all of this.
The recipe is:

00:07:40.590 --> 00:07:44.096
take the force,
take the d by dy

00:07:44.096 --> 00:07:47.940
of F_x,
and compare it to d by

00:07:47.940 --> 00:07:49.920
dx of
F_y,

00:07:49.920 --> 00:07:53.360
and if they're equal,
it's a conservative force.

00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:56.990
That's the summary of last
lecture.

00:07:56.990 --> 00:08:00.160
How much of a detail you want
to know is entirely up to you.

00:08:05.120 --> 00:08:12.293
Okay, so now--so I'm going
to--This is residual from last

00:08:12.293 --> 00:08:16.088
time.
So, I'm going to basically hide

00:08:16.088 --> 00:08:17.224
that.
If you want,

00:08:17.224 --> 00:08:19.329
you can take a few moments
writing it down.

00:08:19.329 --> 00:08:21.259
But you understand the point
now.

00:08:21.259 --> 00:08:22.758
The point is,
there are--In fact,

00:08:22.758 --> 00:08:25.052
if you think about it,
it's fairly miraculous that

00:08:25.052 --> 00:08:27.627
there are forces in nature so
that the work done by them

00:08:27.627 --> 00:08:30.529
doesn't depend on how you got
from A to B.

00:08:30.529 --> 00:08:34.981
Even more interesting is that
all the fundamental forces that

00:08:34.981 --> 00:08:37.376
we know -- gravity,
electrostatics,

00:08:37.376 --> 00:08:40.331
even the strong force,
weak force, every force that we

00:08:40.331 --> 00:08:43.621
know to the extent it can be
described by a force -- happens

00:08:43.621 --> 00:08:46.525
to be conservative.
So, it's not that we are hung

00:08:46.525 --> 00:08:48.470
up on some rather exceptional
case;

00:08:48.470 --> 00:08:51.960
nature is kind enough that all
the forces are conservative.

00:08:51.960 --> 00:08:53.450
Now, friction is a little
tricky.

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:54.654
You might say,
"Well, friction is not

00:08:54.654 --> 00:08:56.785
conservative."
But friction is not a

00:08:56.785 --> 00:08:59.536
microscopic force;
friction is a gross,

00:08:59.536 --> 00:09:03.522
average way to describe things,
at some real fundamental level

00:09:03.522 --> 00:09:06.070
every force is in fact
conservative.

00:09:06.070 --> 00:09:12.597
Anyway, gravity is conservative
and then the electrostatic force

00:09:12.597 --> 00:09:16.828
is conservative also.
So, when we study conservative

00:09:16.828 --> 00:09:19.970
systems, we are studying
something fairly general.

00:09:19.970 --> 00:09:24.501
So, today I go to one of the
famous conservative problems

00:09:24.501 --> 00:09:27.820
which is the gravitational
interaction.

00:09:27.820 --> 00:09:34.309
So, the situation was as
follows at Newton's time.

00:09:34.309 --> 00:09:38.420
You know that Copernicus
proposed that the way to think

00:09:38.420 --> 00:09:42.759
about our Solar System is to put
the Sun at the center.

00:09:42.759 --> 00:09:47.809
Now, so here is Copernicus'
picture.

00:09:47.809 --> 00:09:49.450
Here's the Sun,
here are the various planets.

00:09:54.179 --> 00:09:56.880
You have to agree that's very
remarkable.

00:09:56.880 --> 00:09:58.795
Okay?
First of all,

00:09:58.795 --> 00:10:01.636
it's remarkable because that
was the period when you--It was

00:10:01.636 --> 00:10:04.139
not "publish or perish" but
"publish and perish."

00:10:04.139 --> 00:10:07.168
It was not a good thing to come
out and say what you thought,

00:10:07.168 --> 00:10:10.705
and he still did that.
Even independent of the social

00:10:10.705 --> 00:10:15.279
risk, how did anybody figure
this out, because even today,

00:10:15.279 --> 00:10:18.320
even when I know this is true,
I look around,

00:10:18.320 --> 00:10:21.500
it doesn't look like this at
all to my eyes.

00:10:21.500 --> 00:10:24.112
So, on a good day,
I flatter myself into thinking

00:10:24.112 --> 00:10:27.159
I could have maybe discovered
this or discovered that.

00:10:27.159 --> 00:10:29.760
There is no way I would have
done this.

00:10:29.760 --> 00:10:31.740
This is really amazing.
Go out and look.

00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:34.440
Because what you are saying is,
if you look at our Solar System

00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:36.400
from far away it's going to look
like this.

00:10:36.400 --> 00:10:39.600
That's fine.
But what is our vantage point?

00:10:39.600 --> 00:10:43.188
We are sitting on third rock
and we're going around and we

00:10:43.188 --> 00:10:47.028
somehow think we are at rest and
everything is spinning around

00:10:47.028 --> 00:10:50.201
the opposite way.
And to deduce from that chaos

00:10:50.201 --> 00:10:52.820
this simple picture is quite
remarkable.

00:10:52.820 --> 00:10:55.917
You got a lot of points just
for saying this is what's

00:10:55.917 --> 00:10:58.944
happened.
That was a big--It was properly

00:10:58.944 --> 00:11:01.559
called the Copernican
Revolution.

00:11:01.559 --> 00:11:04.464
After the Copernican
Revolution, people just said,

00:11:04.464 --> 00:11:08.079
take the data we get with this
as the center and transcribe it

00:11:08.079 --> 00:11:10.450
with that as the center and plot
it.

00:11:10.450 --> 00:11:13.791
So the person,
Tycho Brahe who was a rich guy

00:11:13.791 --> 00:11:17.893
who had his own lab and he
studied the Solar System and

00:11:17.893 --> 00:11:21.918
Kepler was an assistant who
carried on the work for 40

00:11:21.918 --> 00:11:22.830
years.

00:11:27.139 --> 00:11:30.975
For 40 years he studied this
problem and he published his

00:11:30.975 --> 00:11:32.819
answers.
I got to tell you,

00:11:32.819 --> 00:11:36.748
all of you who are going into
science, I would urge you not to

00:11:36.748 --> 00:11:38.809
publish every 40 years,
okay?

00:11:38.809 --> 00:11:41.432
You're not going to get a job,
you're not going to get a

00:11:41.432 --> 00:11:43.529
Ph.D., you're not going to get a
post-doc;

00:11:43.529 --> 00:11:46.779
you'll be a 70-year-old
post-doc, if you do this.

00:11:46.779 --> 00:11:48.600
So, the climate's very
different now.

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:51.529
Even though we have a lot more
money for science,

00:11:51.529 --> 00:11:55.068
I don't think we have science,
we have money for science of

00:11:55.068 --> 00:11:57.994
such long vision.
The only example that comes to

00:11:57.994 --> 00:12:01.283
my mind is a work by Ray Davis
who looked for solar neutrinos

00:12:01.283 --> 00:12:04.494
for about 30 years,
and fortunately his reputation

00:12:04.494 --> 00:12:07.970
was so strong that funding
agencies kept him going.

00:12:07.970 --> 00:12:11.876
He looked at neutrinos from the
Sun for 30 years to be really

00:12:11.876 --> 00:12:15.547
sure that there was a problem,
and he confronted the theorists

00:12:15.547 --> 00:12:18.620
with the problem and the problem
subsequently got resolved.

00:12:18.620 --> 00:12:22.064
But by and large people
published not a paper in 30

00:12:22.064 --> 00:12:26.266
years but rather the goal is 30
papers a year is more what you

00:12:26.266 --> 00:12:28.611
want to do.
But you got to realize that

00:12:28.611 --> 00:12:30.700
we're not much smarter than our
ancestors.

00:12:30.700 --> 00:12:34.591
In fact, the possibility that
we have 30 excellent ideas a

00:12:34.591 --> 00:12:38.229
year is very unlikely.
So, I have to admire somebody

00:12:38.229 --> 00:12:42.434
like Kepler who after 40 years
gave us something that's really

00:12:42.434 --> 00:12:45.370
solid gold,
because that's what triggered,

00:12:45.370 --> 00:12:48.129
that's what set Newton on the
right path.

00:12:48.129 --> 00:12:51.250
So, there are three laws of
Kepler, okay?

00:12:51.250 --> 00:12:55.600
So, three laws in 40 years.
Still better than Congress.

00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:59.551
Here is what he had.
The first law is,

00:12:59.551 --> 00:13:06.089
"All planets go around the Sun
on an elliptical orbit with the

00:13:06.089 --> 00:13:09.737
Sun as the focus."
So, I'm not going to write all

00:13:09.737 --> 00:13:11.879
the words, it'll take me forever
to write it;

00:13:11.879 --> 00:13:16.334
I'll just say "elliptical
orbit," and you guys can get the

00:13:16.334 --> 00:13:19.460
precise text from any source you
like.

00:13:19.460 --> 00:13:21.981
But I have to remind you what
elliptical orbit means,

00:13:21.981 --> 00:13:23.790
right?
So everyone has to know what an

00:13:23.790 --> 00:13:25.714
ellipse is.
So, you draw a circle,

00:13:25.714 --> 00:13:28.838
you take a thumbtack,
you stick it into your table,

00:13:28.838 --> 00:13:31.695
you take a string,
form a loop like that,

00:13:31.695 --> 00:13:34.996
put a pencil here,
and keep the pencil tight and

00:13:34.996 --> 00:13:37.051
walk around,
keeping the distance,

00:13:37.051 --> 00:13:39.301
you get a circle.
For an ellipse,

00:13:39.301 --> 00:13:44.404
you take two thumbtacks and you
take a string like this,

00:13:44.404 --> 00:13:48.950
keeping that length plus that
length constant,

00:13:48.950 --> 00:13:51.741
and you move,
keeping the string tight,

00:13:51.741 --> 00:13:54.899
and the shape you produce is
the ellipse.

00:13:54.899 --> 00:13:58.037
And these are the two focal
points, F_1 and

00:13:58.037 --> 00:14:01.069
F_2.
An ellipse is an egg-shaped

00:14:01.069 --> 00:14:04.622
circle and if you want to get
the circle back from the

00:14:04.622 --> 00:14:06.480
ellipse,
you just move the two focal

00:14:06.480 --> 00:14:08.680
points to a single point,
and you'll get the circle.

00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:15.815
Whereas a circle has only a
single number R,

00:14:15.815 --> 00:14:20.299
the radius characterizing it,
the ellipse has what's called a

00:14:20.299 --> 00:14:23.614
major axis and a minor axis;
and major axis,

00:14:23.614 --> 00:14:26.757
2a, and a is
called a semi-major axis,

00:14:26.757 --> 00:14:31.344
which is that distance.
So, do you know how you can get

00:14:31.344 --> 00:14:34.445
an ellipse?
Why the Greeks were studying

00:14:34.445 --> 00:14:36.400
ellipses?
Where they come from?

00:14:36.400 --> 00:14:40.346
Yes?
Student: If you take two

00:14:40.346 --> 00:14:44.038
points and you have one x
as a reflection of another one

00:14:44.038 --> 00:14:47.136
and you use the plane as a
section to cut through the

00:14:47.136 --> 00:14:49.101
[inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:14:49.101 --> 00:14:52.102
Shankar: Right,
these are called--

00:14:52.102 --> 00:14:56.379
Student: [inaudible]
cones at different angles,

00:14:56.379 --> 00:14:59.772
the outline of these cones,
if you cut a section,

00:14:59.772 --> 00:15:01.577
will be elliptical,
circular [inaudible]

00:15:01.577 --> 00:15:03.660
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Right.

00:15:03.660 --> 00:15:06.249
They'll be ellipse, circles;
they'll be various famous

00:15:06.249 --> 00:15:08.432
geometric figures.
I think for our purpose,

00:15:08.432 --> 00:15:11.387
even if you took a single cone
and you cut it at some angle,

00:15:11.387 --> 00:15:14.660
that would be an ellipse.
That's why the Greeks were

00:15:14.660 --> 00:15:17.124
studying this.
But you need a second cone for

00:15:17.124 --> 00:15:18.442
other things.
But for now,

00:15:18.442 --> 00:15:21.970
if you slice a cone parallel to
the base, you'll get a circle;

00:15:21.970 --> 00:15:23.730
at an angle,
you'll get the ellipse.

00:15:23.730 --> 00:15:27.514
So, that's the first statement.
Second statement is the

00:15:27.514 --> 00:15:33.347
following: If you pick one
planet and it's there today,

00:15:33.347 --> 00:15:37.667
you wait a week,
it's there, and you wait

00:15:37.667 --> 00:15:43.302
another week it's there.
You join these two lines and

00:15:43.302 --> 00:15:49.200
you call that the area swept out
by the planet in the first week;

00:15:49.200 --> 00:15:53.860
then, in the second week,
the area swept out is that.

00:15:53.860 --> 00:15:56.838
So, it's the area intercepted
by the two radial vectors and

00:15:56.838 --> 00:16:00.053
the arc along which you move.
And Kepler said the rate at

00:16:00.053 --> 00:16:03.720
which the area is swept out --
let dA/dt be a shorthand

00:16:03.720 --> 00:16:07.327
for how much area is covered in
a certain time -- so you take

00:16:07.327 --> 00:16:09.483
area swept out,
divide by Ît,

00:16:09.483 --> 00:16:10.890
and he said that's a constant.

00:16:16.870 --> 00:16:23.199
And the third result is that,
let me see, the square of the

00:16:23.199 --> 00:16:28.220
time it takes a planet to go
around the Sun,

00:16:28.220 --> 00:16:35.953
divided by the cube of the
orbit size, is the same for all

00:16:35.953 --> 00:16:37.310
planets.

00:16:49.320 --> 00:16:51.230
These are the three laws of
Kepler.

00:16:51.230 --> 00:16:54.149
Yes?
Student: So why did you

00:16:54.149 --> 00:16:56.904
write [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:16:56.904 --> 00:17:00.225
Shankar: Well,
you don't need calculus to do

00:17:00.225 --> 00:17:04.193
what I just said.
Calculus says take the limit

00:17:04.193 --> 00:17:07.698
Ît goes to 0.
If Ît is one day or one

00:17:07.698 --> 00:17:11.269
month, it really doesn't matter.
Take a planet like Pluto -- I'm

00:17:11.269 --> 00:17:14.630
going to keep calling it a
planet because I'm attached to

00:17:14.630 --> 00:17:17.990
Pluto more than to some of the
newer guys -- you wait one

00:17:17.990 --> 00:17:19.819
month,
you see how much area is

00:17:19.819 --> 00:17:22.500
covered, then wait another
month, you'll still find it's

00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:24.413
true.
In fact, it happens to be true

00:17:24.413 --> 00:17:26.140
even if it's not
infinitesimally;

00:17:26.140 --> 00:17:29.370
you can wait even finite
periods, but this is the limit.

00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:32.801
Yes?
Student: Are there in

00:17:32.801 --> 00:17:34.980
fact slight deviations from
Kepler's third law?

00:17:34.980 --> 00:17:38.036
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: There are lots of

00:17:38.036 --> 00:17:39.339
deviations.
Student: [inaudible]

00:17:39.339 --> 00:17:40.140
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No.

00:17:40.140 --> 00:17:43.504
Oh, okay.
There are lots of corrections

00:17:43.504 --> 00:17:45.814
to Kepler's laws.
First of all,

00:17:45.814 --> 00:17:48.509
Kepler's law,
if we really observe it very

00:17:48.509 --> 00:17:52.059
carefully, none of these things
will actually work.

00:17:52.059 --> 00:17:54.315
First of all,
planets are not moving just

00:17:54.315 --> 00:17:56.683
around the Sun,
they have the pull of other

00:17:56.683 --> 00:17:59.474
planets.
Secondly, the Newtonian law of

00:17:59.474 --> 00:18:03.562
gravitation, which we'll study
today, has got modifications

00:18:03.562 --> 00:18:07.509
from Einstein's theory,
which also modify the orbits.

00:18:07.509 --> 00:18:09.996
In fact, the truth is the
planets don't follow close

00:18:09.996 --> 00:18:11.799
orbits at all but that the
ellipse,

00:18:11.799 --> 00:18:14.793
instead of starting out this
way and staying this way

00:18:14.793 --> 00:18:17.335
forever, slowly rotates,
and that's called the

00:18:17.335 --> 00:18:19.981
procession of the orbit.
And one of the biggest

00:18:19.981 --> 00:18:22.529
mysteries was Mercury had a
procession.

00:18:22.529 --> 00:18:26.053
In other words,
the orbit was not closing but

00:18:26.053 --> 00:18:30.858
like a Rosetta stone it is doing
this -- not at this rate but

00:18:30.858 --> 00:18:34.246
very, very slowly.
The majority of that procession

00:18:34.246 --> 00:18:37.341
was fully understood by the
effects that I mentioned to you,

00:18:37.341 --> 00:18:39.859
namely the fact there are other
forces on it.

00:18:39.859 --> 00:18:41.900
Jupiter, particularly,
is a very massive planet;

00:18:41.900 --> 00:18:45.309
you cannot ignore this effect.
But still there was a tiny part

00:18:45.309 --> 00:18:48.203
that was missing,
which is 43 degrees of an arc

00:18:48.203 --> 00:18:50.966
per century -- very,
very small deviation,

00:18:50.966 --> 00:18:53.600
left unexplained,
and the general theory of

00:18:53.600 --> 00:18:56.807
relativity filled in that gap.
So, the answer is,

00:18:56.807 --> 00:19:00.281
every law I told you long back
will receive corrections,

00:19:00.281 --> 00:19:05.235
but they're usually very small.
Anyway, this was the data that

00:19:05.235 --> 00:19:09.173
was given to Newton.
So Newton, as you know,

00:19:09.173 --> 00:19:13.978
was sent home from college
because there was a plague and

00:19:13.978 --> 00:19:17.410
he went and lived in his old
village,

00:19:17.410 --> 00:19:22.428
and he was contemplating this
issue, because he had already by

00:19:22.428 --> 00:19:25.720
this time invented the laws of
motion,

00:19:25.720 --> 00:19:29.569
and I think he'd also invented
the basic ideas of calculus.

00:19:29.569 --> 00:19:33.408
There was some debate about who
got there first but there was no

00:19:33.408 --> 00:19:36.525
debate about what happened next.
So Newton said,

00:19:36.525 --> 00:19:40.080
"Okay, I am going to understand
planetary motion."

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:44.244
And so are you.
So, you guys have been terribly

00:19:44.244 --> 00:19:47.010
disappointed that after all the
work you've put in,

00:19:47.010 --> 00:19:50.440
you're still doing inclined
planes and pulleys and whatnot.

00:19:50.440 --> 00:19:53.877
So, today we're going to make a
big leap, because today you're

00:19:53.877 --> 00:19:56.920
going to understand how planets
move around the Sun.

00:19:56.920 --> 00:20:01.143
That's a mega problem, right?
The little ms you put in

00:20:01.143 --> 00:20:03.610
the equation are not mass of a
pulley or a plane,

00:20:03.610 --> 00:20:05.769
but mass of Jupiter or mass of
the Sun.

00:20:05.769 --> 00:20:09.460
So, you're doing something of
cosmological proportions.

00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:13.600
And you don't need to know too
much more to do that.

00:20:13.600 --> 00:20:16.363
You're almost there.
So, I'm going to just tell you

00:20:16.363 --> 00:20:21.018
the one missing thing.
So, what Newton had done is to

00:20:21.018 --> 00:20:27.460
realize that in order to
understand motion of bodies,

00:20:27.460 --> 00:20:31.348
you have to associate a force
with acceleration and not with

00:20:31.348 --> 00:20:33.339
mass.
That was his contribution.

00:20:33.339 --> 00:20:36.920
If you think it's forces that
cause velocity,

00:20:36.920 --> 00:20:40.500
you look at a planet going
around the Sun,

00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:43.266
where the velocity is pointing
in different directions at

00:20:43.266 --> 00:20:45.983
different times and you have to
ask what can possibly be

00:20:45.983 --> 00:20:47.910
propelling the planet in this
loop,

00:20:47.910 --> 00:20:51.039
you don't get any definitive
answer.

00:20:51.039 --> 00:20:53.051
On the other hand,
if you calculate the

00:20:53.051 --> 00:20:56.068
acceleration of the planet,
take the simple case where the

00:20:56.068 --> 00:21:00.196
planet's going on a circle.
The acceleration at every

00:21:00.196 --> 00:21:05.220
instant points towards the Sun.
Okay?

00:21:05.220 --> 00:21:08.795
That's how--That's why it's
important to understand what

00:21:08.795 --> 00:21:12.230
forces are doing.
Forces are causing acceleration.

00:21:12.230 --> 00:21:16.059
So, Newton had already shown us.
And we have done many problems.

00:21:16.059 --> 00:21:18.160
When a body accelerates there's
a reason for it.

00:21:18.160 --> 00:21:21.519
Well, all bodies are
accelerating towards the Sun.

00:21:21.519 --> 00:21:23.540
It's fairly clear what the
reason is.

00:21:23.540 --> 00:21:27.043
The reason is the Sun.
And you then postulate a force

00:21:27.043 --> 00:21:31.435
that's exerted by the Sun on the
planet that bends it into a

00:21:31.435 --> 00:21:34.326
circle.
And your job is to find out

00:21:34.326 --> 00:21:36.740
that force.
What's the nature of the force?

00:21:36.740 --> 00:21:42.683
So, it is again here that
Newton decided that the force

00:21:42.683 --> 00:21:49.397
that bends the planets around
the Sun is the same as the force

00:21:49.397 --> 00:21:53.910
that bends the Moon around the
Earth.

00:21:53.910 --> 00:21:57.610
It was known by then the Moon's
also going around the Earth.

00:21:57.610 --> 00:22:01.199
So, let's look at that problem.
So, here's the Earth,

00:22:01.199 --> 00:22:05.557
and here is the Moon,
and it's going around the

00:22:05.557 --> 00:22:08.379
Earth.
Now, the Moon is accelerating

00:22:08.379 --> 00:22:12.181
towards the Earth and that's
something we have learned in

00:22:12.181 --> 00:22:17.184
this course.
Then, here is the famous apple,

00:22:17.184 --> 00:22:21.940
also accelerating towards the
Earth.

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:26.067
And Newton decided that the
cause behind both the forces is

00:22:26.067 --> 00:22:28.630
a new force, the force of
gravity.

00:22:28.630 --> 00:22:31.380
The same thing that pulls the
apple is what pulls the Moon.

00:22:34.680 --> 00:22:39.137
So, we have to now ask,
"What is the nature of that

00:22:39.137 --> 00:22:42.279
force?"
We're going to write a formula

00:22:42.279 --> 00:22:44.568
for the force.
First, let me look at the

00:22:44.568 --> 00:22:46.393
magnitude.
The direction is very clear,

00:22:46.393 --> 00:22:48.680
it is directed towards the
center of the Earth.

00:22:48.680 --> 00:22:50.925
So, I won't write that down.
Later on I will write you a

00:22:50.925 --> 00:22:52.539
formula with vector symbols in
it;

00:22:52.539 --> 00:22:54.860
so the vector will point
towards the center of the Earth.

00:22:54.860 --> 00:22:57.990
But let's look at the magnitude.
If you take an apple here,

00:22:57.990 --> 00:23:01.279
of mass m,
and you call M the mass

00:23:01.279 --> 00:23:05.768
of the Earth,
near the Earth we all know the

00:23:05.768 --> 00:23:09.809
acceleration of a body is
constant.

00:23:09.809 --> 00:23:13.783
Therefore, it can happen only
if the force depends on the mass

00:23:13.783 --> 00:23:16.765
of the apple.
This force is going to depend

00:23:16.765 --> 00:23:19.292
on various things.
I'm going to write the formula,

00:23:19.292 --> 00:23:21.561
but one thing it depends on,
it's got to be proportional to

00:23:21.561 --> 00:23:24.334
the mass of the apple.
That's because then if you

00:23:24.334 --> 00:23:26.750
divide by m,
to get a,

00:23:26.750 --> 00:23:30.202
the mass drops out and you
understand the fact that

00:23:30.202 --> 00:23:33.930
everything near the Earth falls
at the same rate.

00:23:33.930 --> 00:23:37.556
The only way that can happen is
if the force depends on the mass

00:23:37.556 --> 00:23:40.808
of the apple.
We agreed that that m

00:23:40.808 --> 00:23:42.599
belongs there,
okay?

00:23:42.599 --> 00:23:45.339
If it doesn't belong there,
if you have something that

00:23:45.339 --> 00:23:47.391
depends on m squared,
for example,

00:23:47.391 --> 00:23:49.020
or it doesn't depend on
m at all,

00:23:49.020 --> 00:23:51.689
you have a problem.
If the force doesn't depend on

00:23:51.689 --> 00:23:55.072
the mass at all -- suppose the
force on every body near the

00:23:55.072 --> 00:23:58.630
Earth was a constant force --
and then you divide by mass,

00:23:58.630 --> 00:24:00.948
you'll find that heavier
objects will have a smaller

00:24:00.948 --> 00:24:03.049
acceleration;
but that's not what you find.

00:24:03.049 --> 00:24:06.049
So, there's a perfect and
precise cancellation on the mass

00:24:06.049 --> 00:24:08.206
of the object,
all things fall at the same

00:24:08.206 --> 00:24:10.088
rate;
so I know I need this m

00:24:10.088 --> 00:24:13.140
here.
What else do I need?

00:24:13.140 --> 00:24:16.639
You notice that from the Third
Law of Newton,

00:24:16.639 --> 00:24:20.934
if there's a force on the
apple, the apple must exert a

00:24:20.934 --> 00:24:25.247
similar force on the Earth.
So, if you take an example in

00:24:25.247 --> 00:24:28.816
which here's the Earth and
here's the apple -- there's an

00:24:28.816 --> 00:24:32.384
m sitting there -- but
imagine the apple's getting

00:24:32.384 --> 00:24:35.845
bigger and bigger;
the formula's not going to

00:24:35.845 --> 00:24:38.133
change.
Make it bigger and bigger and

00:24:38.133 --> 00:24:41.017
bigger, and bigger,
till it looks like the apple is

00:24:41.017 --> 00:24:43.210
that big and the Earth is that
big.

00:24:43.210 --> 00:24:47.809
Then, you will have to agree
that from that point of view you

00:24:47.809 --> 00:24:52.640
should also have the mass of the
Earth here, playing a symmetric

00:24:52.640 --> 00:24:56.788
role.
So, these two masses have to be

00:24:56.788 --> 00:24:59.273
there.
But then what else should I

00:24:59.273 --> 00:25:02.870
have there, what are the other
variables in the problem?

00:25:02.870 --> 00:25:05.588
Yes?
Student: The distance

00:25:05.588 --> 00:25:06.401
from [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:25:06.401 --> 00:25:07.299
Shankar: The distance
between them.

00:25:07.299 --> 00:25:10.000
And I don't know what the
distance dependence is.

00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:14.895
I'm going to say that it's some
function of the distance between

00:25:14.895 --> 00:25:16.960
them.
So, we don't know what the

00:25:16.960 --> 00:25:19.369
distance is.
All right?

00:25:19.369 --> 00:25:22.259
So, let's find the acceleration
of the apple.

00:25:22.259 --> 00:25:26.031
That happens to be the mass of
the Earth, this function,

00:25:26.031 --> 00:25:29.940
with r calculated to be
the radius of the Earth.

00:25:35.130 --> 00:25:40.264
Then, you go to the Moon and
you ask, "What's the

00:25:40.264 --> 00:25:44.593
acceleration of the Moon?"
It's the mass of the Earth

00:25:44.593 --> 00:25:47.158
times the same function,
at the radius of the lunar

00:25:47.158 --> 00:25:47.620
orbit.

00:25:53.140 --> 00:25:56.510
Does anybody know how far the
Moon is?

00:25:56.510 --> 00:25:59.330
Any guess?
Do you know how far it is?

00:25:59.330 --> 00:26:05.940
Make a wild guess.
Student: A million miles.

00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:06.960
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: A million miles.

00:26:06.960 --> 00:26:10.900
Not bad, but not quite there.
Any other guess?

00:26:10.900 --> 00:26:13.640
Yes?
Student: 250,000.

00:26:13.640 --> 00:26:15.920
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Pretty close,

00:26:15.920 --> 00:26:18.154
238,000 miles.
So, that's a quarter of a

00:26:18.154 --> 00:26:20.130
million miles.
So, a million's not bad.

00:26:20.130 --> 00:26:22.105
Okay?
If you make an estimate that's

00:26:22.105 --> 00:26:24.614
off by a factor of Ï,
in physics, it's fine,

00:26:24.614 --> 00:26:27.468
but if you say ten miles or
something then we should have a

00:26:27.468 --> 00:26:30.101
talk;
we should have a very long talk

00:26:30.101 --> 00:26:32.180
after class.
Okay, so that's correct.

00:26:32.180 --> 00:26:37.609
So, this guy is 240,000 miles,
just to be simple.

00:26:37.609 --> 00:26:39.150
The radius of the Earth,
how about that?

00:26:42.700 --> 00:26:44.748
Yes?
Student: [inaudible]

00:26:44.748 --> 00:26:47.384
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: How about in good

00:26:47.384 --> 00:26:53.368
old-fashioned miles?
Student: 3 times 10 to

