Professor Ramamurti

00:29:07.662 --> 00:29:08.654
Shankar: Yes.
Student: Is that why

00:29:08.654 --> 00:29:09.509
it's that way,
v^(2)/R?

00:29:09.509 --> 00:29:10.185
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Right,

00:29:10.185 --> 00:29:11.448
exactly.
In fact, if it's not a circle

00:29:11.448 --> 00:29:14.076
it's much more complicated.
So, in this calculation we'll

00:29:14.076 --> 00:29:17.218
assume everything is a circle;
it turns out to be not so bad,

00:29:17.218 --> 00:29:19.334
even for planets.
So, if you do the

00:29:19.334 --> 00:29:22.602
v^(2)/R,
you put the numbers in and you

00:29:22.602 --> 00:29:26.741
find the acceleration of the
apple is 3600 times more than

00:29:26.741 --> 00:29:31.356
the acceleration of the Moon.
On the other hand,

00:29:31.356 --> 00:29:38.990
you find the apple and the Moon
radii are a factor of 60 apart.

00:29:38.990 --> 00:29:40.938
In other words,
the Moon is 60 times as far

00:29:40.938 --> 00:29:42.980
from the center of the Earth as
the apple.

00:29:42.980 --> 00:29:45.819
And you look at 60,
you look at 3600,

00:29:45.819 --> 00:29:48.209
right?
You don't have to be a Newton

00:29:48.209 --> 00:29:52.486
to figure out what's going on;
then you therefore write down

00:29:52.486 --> 00:29:54.140
this great formula.

00:29:58.289 --> 00:30:01.152
Do you understand now that the
r^(2)--how you get the

00:30:01.152 --> 00:30:03.714
r^(2)?
Again, it's pretty remarkable

00:30:03.714 --> 00:30:07.700
because this is going to be an
r to the power of 2.001,

00:30:07.700 --> 00:30:10.436
and you would certainly not
know you're wrong because these

00:30:10.436 --> 00:30:12.869
numbers are not known that well.
Newton just said,

00:30:12.869 --> 00:30:14.969
look, let me take the nearest
integer power,

00:30:14.969 --> 00:30:17.410
this looks like close enough to
1/r^(2).

00:30:17.410 --> 00:30:20.638
It happens to be 1/r^(2)
is a fantastically good

00:30:20.638 --> 00:30:22.910
approximation to the Law of
Gravity.

00:30:22.910 --> 00:30:24.920
So, we were also quite
fortunate there;

00:30:24.920 --> 00:30:28.410
the laws of gravity didn't have
to be that simple.

00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:33.185
Okay, so now are we done,
or should I do something else

00:30:33.185 --> 00:30:34.697
to this?
Student: [inaudible]

00:30:34.697 --> 00:30:35.789
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Pardon me?

00:30:35.789 --> 00:30:38.371
Student: [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:30:38.371 --> 00:30:41.650
Shankar: This is the force.
I need what else now?

00:30:41.650 --> 00:30:43.550
Student: [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:30:43.550 --> 00:30:45.762
Shankar: One of you has to
put your hand up and take a

00:30:45.762 --> 00:30:47.520
stand.
Yes, you have to say something?

00:30:47.520 --> 00:30:49.206
Student: A constant.
Professor Ramamurti

00:30:49.206 --> 00:30:50.030
Shankar: A constant,
right.

00:30:50.030 --> 00:30:53.163
Why do you need the constant?
Student: Because if you

00:30:53.163 --> 00:30:56.708
just multiply what you had on
the board, you probably wouldn't

00:30:56.708 --> 00:30:58.530
get exactly the answer.
Professor Ramamurti

00:30:58.530 --> 00:30:59.730
Shankar: Very good.
Yes?

00:30:59.730 --> 00:31:02.254
Student: If you look at
the units, they don't match very

00:31:02.254 --> 00:31:02.949
good.
Professor Ramamurti

00:31:02.949 --> 00:31:03.750
Shankar: The units don't
match, right?

00:31:03.750 --> 00:31:07.070
So, if some kid called,
Isaac comes to you and says,

00:31:07.070 --> 00:31:09.349
"I got this new law of
gravitation",

00:31:09.349 --> 00:31:12.280
I would say "Go back and fix
your units."

00:31:12.280 --> 00:31:14.977
The units don't match.
But not only that,

00:31:14.977 --> 00:31:18.380
I think some of you had another
objection, that if you took the

00:31:18.380 --> 00:31:21.398
mass of the Earth and mass of
the Moon and the apple and

00:31:21.398 --> 00:31:24.487
divided by the radius,
you'll get a number that won't

00:31:24.487 --> 00:31:27.809
agree with the force of gravity
near the Earth as we know it.

00:31:27.809 --> 00:31:30.189
So the point is,
when a function is proportional

00:31:30.189 --> 00:31:32.062
to all these things,
there is always a

00:31:32.062 --> 00:31:34.973
proportionality constant.
And the constants--One of the

00:31:34.973 --> 00:31:37.761
purposes of a constant is to
make the dimensions come out

00:31:37.761 --> 00:31:39.924
right;
the other is to make the values

00:31:39.924 --> 00:31:42.630
come out right.
Because I got to make sure that

00:31:42.630 --> 00:31:46.388
when I apply it to an apple near
the Earth, I put the mass of the

00:31:46.388 --> 00:31:49.089
apple, and let's say I divide by
the apple.

00:31:49.089 --> 00:31:52.290
This whole thing,
what should it be equal to?

00:31:52.290 --> 00:31:54.357
Student: 9.8.
Professor Ramamurti

00:31:54.357 --> 00:31:55.849
Shankar: It's got to be 9.8,
you understand that?

00:31:55.849 --> 00:31:59.900
The acceleration of the apple,
near the Earth,

00:31:59.900 --> 00:32:02.931
has to be 9.8.
If I put the radius of the

00:32:02.931 --> 00:32:07.676
Earth here, this better be 9.8.
So you pick a number g,

00:32:07.676 --> 00:32:12.321
which is some number,
6 times 10 to the minus11 and

00:32:12.321 --> 00:32:17.430
the units for g are some
number times Newton,

00:32:17.430 --> 00:32:23.765
m^(2) or kg^(2).
That'll make the units come out

00:32:23.765 --> 00:32:26.429
right.
So that's called a G,

00:32:26.429 --> 00:32:30.445
that's the law of--It's the
universal gravitational

00:32:30.445 --> 00:32:34.348
constant.
I'm almost ready to write down

00:32:34.348 --> 00:32:40.720
now the great Newtonian law.
The great Newtonian law says

00:32:40.720 --> 00:32:47.151
F = GmM/r^(2),
where these are two objects of

00:32:47.151 --> 00:32:49.858
mass;
m and M are at a

00:32:49.858 --> 00:32:51.840
distance r from each
other.

00:32:51.840 --> 00:32:54.759
But it's not yet a vector;
this is just a number.

00:32:54.759 --> 00:32:58.488
So, I want to say that if this
is one mass and here's the other

00:32:58.488 --> 00:33:01.031
mass.
I want to say this one feels a

00:33:01.031 --> 00:33:04.852
force towards the center.
So, let me take the Earth to be

00:33:04.852 --> 00:33:07.380
the center here.
I want the force on the Moon.

00:33:07.380 --> 00:33:10.150
I want a vector pointing
towards the center.

00:33:10.150 --> 00:33:13.173
So, I know one vector that's
pointing away from the second

00:33:13.173 --> 00:33:15.720
vector, which is the position
vector r.

00:33:15.720 --> 00:33:19.653
But if I divide that by the
length of the position vector

00:33:19.653 --> 00:33:23.166
r, I think all of you
know enough vectors to

00:33:23.166 --> 00:33:26.609
understand,
this vector has a length 1,

00:33:26.609 --> 00:33:29.529
and points away from the
center.

00:33:29.529 --> 00:33:34.546
But I want it to be pointing
towards the center and that is

00:33:34.546 --> 00:33:39.648
then the force of gravity on the
Moon or on the apple or any

00:33:39.648 --> 00:33:42.443
object.
If I'm thinking of one fixed

00:33:42.443 --> 00:33:46.130
object, like the Earth,
this is the force on the apple.

00:33:46.130 --> 00:33:49.301
If you're thinking of two
objects of comparable size,

00:33:49.301 --> 00:33:52.839
you'll have to say the force on
one is due to the other.

00:33:52.839 --> 00:33:55.299
When you write the formula,
then you've got to make sure

00:33:55.299 --> 00:33:57.670
that the force on one is
pointing to the other one,

00:33:57.670 --> 00:34:00.180
and the force on that guy is
pointing towards this guy.

00:34:00.180 --> 00:34:03.150
So, there is no universal
symbol for all those things.

00:34:03.150 --> 00:34:06.185
I will write it in the simple
case where we imagine at the

00:34:06.185 --> 00:34:08.374
center some massive object,
like the Sun,

00:34:08.374 --> 00:34:10.950
and something tiny going around
it, and the center of

00:34:10.950 --> 00:34:13.675
coordinates is chosen to be at
the center of the massive

00:34:13.675 --> 00:34:16.181
object.
This is the force on the little

00:34:16.181 --> 00:34:19.059
guy.
This is the Law of Gravity.

00:34:19.059 --> 00:34:22.790
It's called the Law of
Universal Gravitation because it

00:34:22.790 --> 00:34:25.469
really is universal.
You got to realize that.

00:34:25.469 --> 00:34:29.115
It's a tremendous leap of faith
to believe that the laws that

00:34:29.115 --> 00:34:32.760
are operative near the surface
of the Earth also apply to the

00:34:32.760 --> 00:34:35.130
Moon and also apply to the
planets.

00:34:35.130 --> 00:34:38.420
This was the year
1600-and-something;

00:34:38.420 --> 00:34:41.409
there was witchcraft and people
had all kinds of superstitions.

00:34:41.409 --> 00:34:44.150
People were not even thinking
in scientific ways.

00:34:44.150 --> 00:34:46.614
There were a lot of illusions
about what the heavens are made

00:34:46.614 --> 00:34:48.328
of.
To believe they're made up of

00:34:48.328 --> 00:34:50.670
similar stuff and controlled by
the same laws,

00:34:50.670 --> 00:34:53.687
that's very obvious now but it
was very far from obvious in

00:34:53.687 --> 00:34:57.010
those days.
It's a tremendous leap of faith.

00:34:57.010 --> 00:35:00.033
And luckily for us that leap of
faith is justified because the

00:35:00.033 --> 00:35:03.187
laws of gravitation--In fact,
the laws of physics that we

00:35:03.187 --> 00:35:06.481
deduce near the Earth seemed to
work all over the entire

00:35:06.481 --> 00:35:08.695
universe.
If you've seen pictures and

00:35:08.695 --> 00:35:11.132
nova of where we are in the
scheme of things,

00:35:11.132 --> 00:35:13.679
we are in a very tiny part of
the universe,

00:35:13.679 --> 00:35:18.119
sampling a tiny volume,
over a tiny period of time.

00:35:18.119 --> 00:35:21.683
But we apply those equations to
the far end of the galaxy,

00:35:21.683 --> 00:35:25.247
the far end of the universe,
and going all the way back to

00:35:25.247 --> 00:35:28.761
the Big Bang.
And we predict the future fate

00:35:28.761 --> 00:35:32.103
of the universe.
So, we assume that the laws

00:35:32.103 --> 00:35:35.792
that we discover here,
now, are valid everywhere and

00:35:35.792 --> 00:35:38.323
at all times.
So far that seems to be true,

00:35:38.323 --> 00:35:40.833
and that's a big break for us,
but for that you really

00:35:40.833 --> 00:35:42.995
couldn't do anything.
If the laws you discovered

00:35:42.995 --> 00:35:44.888
today are not valid tomorrow,
you cannot make any

00:35:44.888 --> 00:35:47.546
predictions.
So, it's another unwritten

00:35:47.546 --> 00:35:52.156
benefit we got -- unspoken --
it's a great benefit that the

00:35:52.156 --> 00:35:56.233
laws you find are universal.
Somebody had to stick his neck

00:35:56.233 --> 00:35:58.869
out and say, this is one of the
first occasions.

00:35:58.869 --> 00:36:03.446
So now, you are going to apply
this law to understand what

00:36:03.446 --> 00:36:07.073
Kepler did.
Okay, so what do you have to do

00:36:07.073 --> 00:36:11.000
to do what Kepler did?
So, we are going to consider

00:36:11.000 --> 00:36:13.800
the motion of a planet around
the Sun.

00:36:13.800 --> 00:36:17.219
So, let's put the Sun here;
let's put the planet here.

00:36:17.219 --> 00:36:18.900
The planet's at the location
r.

00:36:21.940 --> 00:36:25.669
You go back,
as usual, to the only equation

00:36:25.669 --> 00:36:28.942
in town: F = ma.
Now F,

00:36:28.942 --> 00:36:33.559
I told you, has to be deduced
every time with painstaking,

00:36:33.559 --> 00:36:36.030
experimental data.
Without that,

00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:39.036
F = ma is useless.
If you don't know what's on the

00:36:39.036 --> 00:36:41.069
left-hand side,
independently--Let me repeat

00:36:41.069 --> 00:36:43.860
again, you don't say the force
on the body is ma.

00:36:43.860 --> 00:36:46.587
The force on the body is due to
a spring, due to gravity,

00:36:46.587 --> 00:36:49.087
due to charges -- whatever.
You have to do some work to

00:36:49.087 --> 00:36:50.938
find this;
then, you put it into that

00:36:50.938 --> 00:36:52.889
equation.
But let's put it in here.

00:36:52.889 --> 00:36:56.527
The right-hand side of Newton's
law can be written once and for

00:36:56.527 --> 00:36:58.688
all: d^(2)r.
Now, I'm writing

00:36:58.688 --> 00:37:02.110
d^(2)r/dt^(2) because I'm
living in two dimensions.

00:37:02.110 --> 00:37:06.062
Now, on the left-hand side,
I have this new result,

00:37:06.062 --> 00:37:09.936
GMm/r^(2) times--I'm
going to use a symbol,

00:37:09.936 --> 00:37:13.019
r-hat,
which is very common;

00:37:13.019 --> 00:37:16.189
r- anything with a hat on it is
a vector of unit length,

00:37:16.189 --> 00:37:19.590
pointing in the direction of
the regular vector r.

00:37:19.590 --> 00:37:22.492
So if you want,
if r is the position

00:37:22.492 --> 00:37:25.809
vector of an object,
whose length is r,

00:37:25.809 --> 00:37:29.521
r-hat is a little guy
whose length is 1,

00:37:29.521 --> 00:37:32.990
and which points in the radial
direction.

00:37:32.990 --> 00:37:36.368
So, this is your equation.
It's then a problem in

00:37:36.368 --> 00:37:40.661
calculus, to solve the equation,
and everything Kepler said

00:37:40.661 --> 00:37:44.304
should come out of that.
You should find that planets

00:37:44.304 --> 00:37:46.360
like to move in elliptical
orbits.

00:37:46.360 --> 00:37:49.900
You should find the areas swept
out as a constant.

00:37:49.900 --> 00:37:53.044
You should find the square of a
time period is proportional to

00:37:53.044 --> 00:37:56.870
the cube of the orbit size.
Now, if I give this to you as a

00:37:56.870 --> 00:38:00.929
homework problem in the class,
I dare say it'll be very

00:38:00.929 --> 00:38:04.099
difficult for most of you.
I don't know what kind of

00:38:04.099 --> 00:38:06.365
background you have.
You have done some calculus,

00:38:06.365 --> 00:38:08.793
but it's not easy.
But remarkably,

00:38:08.793 --> 00:38:11.989
Newton also solved this
problem.

00:38:11.989 --> 00:38:15.387
Even now when I teach in
Physics 400-and-something,

00:38:15.387 --> 00:38:18.989
for advanced mechanics,
it takes awhile to know how to

00:38:18.989 --> 00:38:21.763
solve this equation.
It's one thing to write it

00:38:21.763 --> 00:38:24.534
down, another thing to actually
solve it and get the ellipse out

00:38:24.534 --> 00:38:26.870
of it.
So Newton did that too.

00:38:26.870 --> 00:38:31.719
So, it's really amazing.
That's why he's such a giant.

00:38:31.719 --> 00:38:34.884
And you have to step back to
that period in time and ask,

00:38:34.884 --> 00:38:37.822
what did one person accomplish
over a period of what,

00:38:37.822 --> 00:38:41.484
five years?
So, that was how physics is

00:38:41.484 --> 00:38:44.467
always done.
Somebody looks at the data,

00:38:44.467 --> 00:38:47.542
sometimes summarizes the data
in the form of certain

00:38:47.542 --> 00:38:50.351
phenomenological facts,
like the laws of Kepler,

00:38:50.351 --> 00:38:53.405
and somebody else has to --
like a theoretical person -- has

00:38:53.405 --> 00:38:56.510
to figure out what are the
underlying rules of this game,

00:38:56.510 --> 00:39:00.207
write it in mathematical form,
and solve the mathematics and

00:39:00.207 --> 00:39:02.738
verify it.
Just imagine that you wrote

00:39:02.738 --> 00:39:05.440
this equation but you couldn't
solve it.

00:39:05.440 --> 00:39:09.739
What you would be saying would
actually be correct.

00:39:09.739 --> 00:39:11.615
You, in fact,
have found the correct law of

00:39:11.615 --> 00:39:14.071
gravity but you can never be
sure it's right because you

00:39:14.071 --> 00:39:16.260
cannot find the consequence of
your equation.

00:39:16.260 --> 00:39:20.180
That is not unheard of.
That's happening in physics

00:39:20.180 --> 00:39:21.298
today.
For example,

00:39:21.298 --> 00:39:24.824
there's the Theory of Quarks.
The quarks are attracted to

00:39:24.824 --> 00:39:27.539
each other by a certain
mechanism we know.

00:39:27.539 --> 00:39:30.606
We know the underlying force
law and from that we're supposed

00:39:30.606 --> 00:39:33.519
to find the--understand the
existence of all particles,

00:39:33.519 --> 00:39:35.730
like protons and neutrons and
so on.

00:39:35.730 --> 00:39:39.953
We do not yet have a way to
show without any doubt that the

00:39:39.953 --> 00:39:44.322
underlying equations imply the
phenomenon that we see when we

00:39:44.322 --> 00:39:47.090
apply it to the problem of
quarks.

00:39:47.090 --> 00:39:50.416
By putting it on a big computer
we are fairly certain that's

00:39:50.416 --> 00:39:52.345
correct.
That will be like solving

00:39:52.345 --> 00:39:55.263
Newton's laws on a computer;
but what Newton did was didn't

00:39:55.263 --> 00:39:57.530
solve it on a computer but
solved it analytically.

00:39:57.530 --> 00:39:59.064
So quite often,
in the past,

00:39:59.064 --> 00:40:02.417
whenever a theory is accepted,
it's because the consequences

00:40:02.417 --> 00:40:05.429
can be worked out and compared
to the experiment.

00:40:05.429 --> 00:40:08.126
But you could be in a position
where you have the right theory

00:40:08.126 --> 00:40:10.469
and the right equations,
but you cannot solve them.

00:40:10.469 --> 00:40:13.550
Anyway, this one happens to be
solvable.

00:40:13.550 --> 00:40:17.199
If I change the force law to
1/r to the 2.1,

00:40:17.199 --> 00:40:21.880
then it's a different story.
Anyway, so we want to solve it

00:40:21.880 --> 00:40:25.320
but we cannot do the ellipse;
it's too hard.

00:40:25.320 --> 00:40:27.570
So, we are going to do the
circle.

00:40:27.570 --> 00:40:30.045
We're going to take the orbit
to be circular,

00:40:30.045 --> 00:40:33.365
and we're going to apply this
force law to that and see what

00:40:33.365 --> 00:40:35.570
we can get.
So, let's do that.

00:40:35.570 --> 00:40:40.332
We can ask ourselves,
"Can a planet have a circular

00:40:40.332 --> 00:40:45.690
orbit of radius r?"
We go back to F = ma.

00:40:45.690 --> 00:40:48.130
Now, you guys are experts on
the right-hand side now.

00:40:48.130 --> 00:40:51.869
We're assuming the planet moves
around the circle at constant

00:40:51.869 --> 00:40:54.815
velocity, at constant speed.
We want to ask,

00:40:54.815 --> 00:40:58.286
"Can such an orbit exist?"
You're always allowed in an

00:40:58.286 --> 00:41:01.587
equation to make an assumption
and plug it in and see if it

00:41:01.587 --> 00:41:03.378
works.
If the left-hand side and the

00:41:03.378 --> 00:41:04.789
right-hand side match,
you win.

00:41:04.789 --> 00:41:06.820
Nobody will ask you any more
questions.

00:41:06.820 --> 00:41:10.650
So, we're asking for a modest
goal.

00:41:10.650 --> 00:41:14.023
Can I find an orbit of a planet
going around at a constant speed

00:41:14.023 --> 00:41:15.630
around the Sun,
on a circle?

00:41:15.630 --> 00:41:19.310
Let the constant speed be
v, then ma,

00:41:19.310 --> 00:41:22.550
everyone seems to know is
mv^(2)/r.

00:41:22.550 --> 00:41:26.389
And it's pointing towards the
center.

00:41:26.389 --> 00:41:30.146
That's should be equal to the
force pointing towards the

00:41:30.146 --> 00:41:33.425
center, and Newton has told us
what the force is:

00:41:33.425 --> 00:41:34.860
GMm/r^(2).

00:41:41.090 --> 00:41:43.979
Everybody understand now?
The left-hand side is the

00:41:43.979 --> 00:41:45.960
effect, the right-hand side is
the cause.

00:41:45.960 --> 00:41:48.316
If you're spinning a rock,
spinning it in a circle,

00:41:48.316 --> 00:41:51.191
that also has an acceleration
toward the center but the string

00:41:51.191 --> 00:41:53.877
is providing the force and you
can work out the force of a

00:41:53.877 --> 00:41:55.340
string,
of the string.

00:41:55.340 --> 00:41:58.836
Here, it's the unseen force of
gravity from the Sun reaching

00:41:58.836 --> 00:42:00.969
out to a planet and pulling it
in.

00:42:00.969 --> 00:42:04.243
And Newton tells you the
formula, deduced from

00:42:04.243 --> 00:42:06.716
terrestrial and lunar
observations,

00:42:06.716 --> 00:42:10.781
now applied to planets.
Okay, so this is something that

00:42:10.781 --> 00:42:14.510
should make you very happy
because this is a very simple

00:42:14.510 --> 00:42:19.066
application of F = ma,
but you're describing planetary

00:42:19.066 --> 00:42:22.253
motion now.
So, these are all masses of big

00:42:22.253 --> 00:42:26.145
guys, the Earth and the Sun.
So let's cancel the r,

00:42:26.145 --> 00:42:30.099
and I get--cancel the mass.
That's very interesting.

00:42:30.099 --> 00:42:37.650
So, that says v^(2)r =
GM.

00:42:37.650 --> 00:42:40.539
It says, yes,
you can have a circular orbit

00:42:40.539 --> 00:42:44.185
of any radius you like,
provided you move at the speed

00:42:44.185 --> 00:42:46.180
satisfying this equation.

00:42:49.320 --> 00:42:51.615
And as long as you satisfy the
equation, I don't care if the

00:42:51.615 --> 00:42:53.599
thing you're spinning is a
satellite or a potato,

00:42:53.599 --> 00:42:55.730
because the mass of the object
drops out.

00:42:55.730 --> 00:42:58.942
So, the condition for orbit is
independent of the object

00:42:58.942 --> 00:43:01.686
orbiting, again,
due to this cancellation of the

00:43:01.686 --> 00:43:05.216
mass on both sides.
All right, so this is all we

00:43:05.216 --> 00:43:09.100
can get out of Newton's laws.
So, let's go back to Kepler.

00:43:09.100 --> 00:43:12.510
Is the orbit possible?
Well, if you say an ellipse--a

00:43:12.510 --> 00:43:15.535
circle is a special case of the
ellipse, you have shown circular

00:43:15.535 --> 00:43:19.164
orbits are possible.
How about equal areas in equal

00:43:19.164 --> 00:43:21.081
time?
It's obviously true in this

00:43:21.081 --> 00:43:23.590
problem because it's going at a
constant speed.

00:43:23.590 --> 00:43:26.650
If it goes that far in one
week, it'll go that far in one

00:43:26.650 --> 00:43:29.929
week and everyone can tell the
area swept out is constant.

00:43:29.929 --> 00:43:33.709
So, the only thing left to
knock off is a third assumption,

00:43:33.709 --> 00:43:37.880
the third observation of Kepler
involving the time period [T].

00:43:37.880 --> 00:43:41.773
So, I do the simplest thing.
I say, the velocity of this

00:43:41.773 --> 00:43:45.019
planet is 2Ïr divided by
the time period.

00:43:45.019 --> 00:43:53.222
I put that in here and I get
4Ï^(2)r^(3)/t^(2) is

00:43:53.222 --> 00:43:57.754
GM,
or I find r^(3)/T^(2) is

00:43:57.754 --> 00:44:00.170
equal to--well,
let me write

00:44:00.170 --> 00:44:03.512
T^(2)/r^(3),
because that's how Kepler wrote

00:44:03.512 --> 00:44:07.682
it.
This is T^(2) divided by

00:44:07.682 --> 00:44:13.350
r^(3) is equal to
4Ï^(2)/GM.

00:44:17.349 --> 00:44:21.639
So, that's another result you
got right away and that's the

00:44:21.639 --> 00:44:24.671
third result,
that the time period and the

00:44:24.671 --> 00:44:29.108
orbital radius--Here is--What
did Newton do that went further

00:44:29.108 --> 00:44:31.488
than Kepler?
Can you tell me what he did

00:44:31.488 --> 00:44:33.936
that's a little beyond?
Have you guys verified Kepler's

00:44:33.936 --> 00:44:36.090
laws or have you gone a little
beyond that?

00:44:36.090 --> 00:44:39.976
Yes?
Student: Well,

00:44:39.976 --> 00:44:41.661
Kepler says that
T^(2)/a^(3) is always the

00:44:41.661 --> 00:44:43.099
same but he didn't define what
[inaudible]

00:44:43.099 --> 00:44:45.030
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Exactly right.

00:44:45.030 --> 00:44:48.575
Let me repeat what he said.
Kepler said T^(2)/a^(3)

00:44:48.575 --> 00:44:52.194
is the same thing,
but he didn't tell you what the

00:44:52.194 --> 00:44:55.630
same thing is.
What is the constant?

00:44:55.630 --> 00:44:59.500
Well, now we know that constant
to be 4, known to all of us,

00:44:59.500 --> 00:45:04.365
Ï, known to all of us,
M, mass of the Sun and

00:45:04.365 --> 00:45:09.230
G is the universal
constant of gravitation.

00:45:09.230 --> 00:45:13.669
So, you calculate the value.
A similar thing happened in

00:45:13.669 --> 00:45:16.873
atomic physics.
A high school teacher called

00:45:16.873 --> 00:45:20.909
Balmer was studying the spectral
lines coming out of an atom,

00:45:20.909 --> 00:45:23.782
and they were coming out at
different frequencies,

00:45:23.782 --> 00:45:27.418
and he said all the frequencies
you'd ever see coming out of an

00:45:27.418 --> 00:45:30.760
atom look like some number times
1/1 integer squared,

00:45:30.760 --> 00:45:33.719
times 1 over a different
integer squared.

00:45:33.719 --> 00:45:37.630
He didn't know what the number
was, but it's some constant.

00:45:37.630 --> 00:45:39.449
I mean, he knew the number but
he didn't know.

00:45:39.449 --> 00:45:41.510
He knew the number but he
didn't know where it came from.

00:45:41.510 --> 00:45:44.079
Then, Bohr had his final theory
of the atom.

00:45:44.079 --> 00:45:47.277
It had exactly this form but
this was just not simply a

00:45:47.277 --> 00:45:49.816
constant you put in;
it involved Ï and the

00:45:49.816 --> 00:45:52.119
electric charge and Planck's
constant and everything.

00:45:52.119 --> 00:45:55.152
So, Balmer did for Bohr what
Kepler did for Newton,

00:45:55.152 --> 00:45:58.064
which is to condense a
complicated data into some

00:45:58.064 --> 00:46:01.340
simple form so that theorists
can have a go at it.

00:46:01.340 --> 00:46:04.335
Then once you got the right
answer it's really beautiful how

00:46:04.335 --> 00:46:06.410
everything fits.
We know this is right.

00:46:06.410 --> 00:46:12.080
Okay, this is called a theory.
By the time physicists will

00:46:12.080 --> 00:46:14.934
call something a theory,
they've put it to a lot of

00:46:14.934 --> 00:46:18.099
tests, okay?
It's not to be casually used.

00:46:18.099 --> 00:46:22.213
And if you have the right
theory, you can make a lot of

00:46:22.213 --> 00:46:24.335
predictions.
You can have a theory that

00:46:24.335 --> 00:46:26.325
planets go around the Sun,
because some angels are

00:46:26.325 --> 00:46:28.439
flapping their wings.
And I say, "Where are the

00:46:28.439 --> 00:46:29.293
angels?"
And you say,

00:46:29.293 --> 00:46:31.140
"Well, part of the theory is
you don't see them."

00:46:31.140 --> 00:46:33.590
It's very good.
What's your next prediction?

00:46:33.590 --> 00:46:35.989
Tell me when the next eclipse
is.

00:46:35.989 --> 00:46:39.280
Tell me the meteor headed for
Earth is going to hit or miss.

00:46:39.280 --> 00:46:43.530
Is this comet going to reappear
or is it a one-shot thing?

00:46:43.530 --> 00:46:46.389
If you cannot answer any of
that, you don't have a theory.

00:46:46.389 --> 00:46:49.530
You have an interpretation of
past data that coincides with

00:46:49.530 --> 00:46:51.390
past data.
That's worth nothing.

00:46:51.390 --> 00:46:54.136
Okay?
So, here's an example of how to

00:46:54.136 --> 00:46:59.994
do it right.
Okay, so this thing has got

00:46:59.994 --> 00:47:03.923
enormous power.
It tells you,

00:47:03.923 --> 00:47:08.087
if you find another planet,
you find a new planet tomorrow,

00:47:08.087 --> 00:47:12.179
if you know how far it is,
I'll tell you what a year is in

00:47:12.179 --> 00:47:14.664
that planet.
I'll tell you how long the

00:47:14.664 --> 00:47:17.584
planet takes to go around the
Sun, because T^(2)/r^(3)

00:47:17.584 --> 00:47:19.859
is known to me.
So, if that planet is at a

00:47:19.859 --> 00:47:22.550
certain distance,
I can tell you the time period,

00:47:22.550 --> 00:47:25.873
or if I see it going around the
Sun and I know it's going to

00:47:25.873 --> 00:47:28.070
complete the revolution in 240
years,

00:47:28.070 --> 00:47:32.336
I can tell you how far it is;
that's another power of the

00:47:32.336 --> 00:47:35.927
theory.
Okay, so now you can do a

00:47:35.927 --> 00:47:40.659
variety of problems using this
formula.

00:47:40.659 --> 00:47:43.180
They're all plug-ins,
but I'll just mention one.

00:47:43.180 --> 00:47:46.756
And most problems are like that.
Everything's going to be

00:47:46.756 --> 00:47:50.506
plugging into this formula.
But one interesting example is

00:47:50.506 --> 00:47:52.610
the following.
So, here is the Earth.

00:47:52.610 --> 00:47:58.989
I'm here and I want to watch a
tennis game being played there.

00:47:58.989 --> 00:48:01.702
I have radio waves,
but you know radio waves cannot

00:48:01.702 --> 00:48:03.917
go through the Earth;
they can only travel in

00:48:03.917 --> 00:48:05.745
straight lines.
And the answer to that,

00:48:05.745 --> 00:48:08.006
I think all of you know,
is to have a bunch of

00:48:08.006 --> 00:48:10.841
satellites,
three of them in particular,

00:48:10.841 --> 00:48:14.723
forming a nice triangle,
and if you can talk to this

00:48:14.723 --> 00:48:17.930
satellite from where you are,
that satellite,

00:48:17.930 --> 00:48:21.063
with the help of the other two,
can always see any other point

00:48:21.063 --> 00:48:23.570
you want,
just by bouncing off.

00:48:23.570 --> 00:48:25.941
Okay, you bounce off this,
you can go there and you can

00:48:25.941 --> 00:48:28.261
hit this guy.
So, if you have three

00:48:28.261 --> 00:48:32.928
satellites, they can help you
connect any point on the Earth

00:48:32.928 --> 00:48:37.280
to any other point by reflecting
off the satellites.

00:48:37.280 --> 00:48:39.742
But the important thing is,
the satellites better be where

00:48:39.742 --> 00:48:42.092
you think they are.
If they're constantly moving

00:48:42.092 --> 00:48:44.773
around, it doesn't work.
So, what you really want is

00:48:44.773 --> 00:48:46.889
what's called geosynchronous
satellites.

00:48:46.889 --> 00:48:50.344
They are satellites--Remember,
if I look at the Earth from the

00:48:50.344 --> 00:48:52.736
top, it is spinning.
This is the North Pole and

00:48:52.736 --> 00:48:55.233
they're spinning.
Therefore, these satellites

00:48:55.233 --> 00:48:58.829
should be rotating around the
Earth once every 24 hours.

00:48:58.829 --> 00:49:01.650
Then, if they're on top of your
head today, they'll be on top of

00:49:01.650 --> 00:49:05.880
your head all the time.
Right?

00:49:05.880 --> 00:49:09.091
So, the time period of the
satellite is 24 hours,

00:49:09.091 --> 00:49:12.838
and the only question is at
what altitude should I launch

00:49:12.838 --> 00:49:16.087
them, to go to this formula?
Put in 24 hours,

00:49:16.087 --> 00:49:19.269
write it in seconds,
you will get the radius.

00:49:19.269 --> 00:49:23.566
Then, once you got the radius,
this equation will tell you at

00:49:23.566 --> 00:49:26.860
what velocity they should be put
into orbit.

00:49:26.860 --> 00:49:30.119
That's it, that's how you put
the geosynchronous satellite.

00:49:30.119 --> 00:49:32.590
That's a simple example of
applying the formula.

00:49:32.590 --> 00:49:35.920
I won't give other examples.
But they are always going to be

00:49:35.920 --> 00:49:39.004
finding T from r
or finding r from

00:49:39.004 --> 00:49:41.369
T.
Sometimes you'll know r;

00:49:41.369 --> 00:49:43.450
sometimes you will know
T.

00:49:43.450 --> 00:49:50.679
Any question about this?
Okay.

00:49:50.679 --> 00:49:53.180
Now, I'm going to come to the
question of energy.

00:49:58.530 --> 00:50:01.248
Whenever you have a new force
you can talk about the Law of

00:50:01.248 --> 00:50:03.729
Conservation of Energy.
So, I want to ask myself,

00:50:03.729 --> 00:50:06.295
what's the potential energy I
can associate with a

00:50:06.295 --> 00:50:08.642
gravitational force?
I can ask myself,

00:50:08.642 --> 00:50:10.860
is it even a conservative
force?

00:50:10.860 --> 00:50:13.610
So, let's take the problem in
two stages.

00:50:13.610 --> 00:50:16.595
First of all,
if you're near the Earth,

00:50:16.595 --> 00:50:19.659
everything falls down near the
Earth.

00:50:19.659 --> 00:50:24.364
If that height is y,
then the force of gravity is

00:50:24.364 --> 00:50:29.068
-mg times J,
but J is a unit vector

00:50:29.068 --> 00:50:32.538
in that direction;
the potential energy is then

00:50:32.538 --> 00:50:34.579
mgy and everybody can
check.

00:50:34.579 --> 00:50:37.336
If you take the -y
derivative of this,

00:50:37.336 --> 00:50:40.079
you get the force.
That's the potential energy.

00:50:40.079 --> 00:50:43.757
And therefore,
when a body is falling near the

00:50:43.757 --> 00:50:48.007
surface of the Earth,
we may assert that Â½ mv^(2)

00:50:48.007 --> 00:50:50.696
+ mg,
let me call it height instead

00:50:50.696 --> 00:50:54.006
of y, let me call this
coordinate h instead of

00:50:54.006 --> 00:50:56.145
y;
I don't think it matters too

00:50:56.145 --> 00:50:59.207
much.
That is the total energy and

00:50:59.207 --> 00:51:03.076
that is a constant.
We applied it the other day to

00:51:03.076 --> 00:51:05.236
roller coasters,
going up and down,

00:51:05.236 --> 00:51:08.466
speeding up and slowing down.
It's just that this number will

00:51:08.466 --> 00:51:10.972
not change.
As the roller coaster changes

00:51:10.972 --> 00:51:14.704
the height, the speed must
change, keeping this number

00:51:14.704 --> 00:51:17.918
constant.
But you know this formula is an

00:51:17.918 --> 00:51:24.269
approximation near the Earth.
You want to apply it globally.

00:51:24.269 --> 00:51:28.947
Before going to the global
problem, let me remember one

00:51:28.947 --> 00:51:33.712
more thing, that g =
GM/R_E^(2) because

00:51:33.712 --> 00:51:38.909
when you apply Newton's law to
the surface of the Earth,

00:51:38.909 --> 00:51:42.512
you better get this number
g, when you apply it to

00:51:42.512 --> 00:51:46.172
something near the Earth.
By the way, Newton took a long

